When You Work

About This Page
This page contains all the relevant information when you work.​​​​​​​

  • ​​​​​​​Especially if you recently joined KIT, we recommend that you first read the Policy and Rules at the bottom
  • ​​​​​​​Read Work Remotely, Work at the Office to check the process when you actually working remotely/at the office
  • Find Additional Information to see office related information
  • ​​​​​​​Quick Link on the right side may be useful for your daily work​​​​​​​

If you have any questions about this topic, please reach out to the people from Contact us.​​​​​​​​​​​​


Work from Home section expanded

Work from Home

Flow

  • Punch Start Time on Lysithea
  • Connect to VPN
  • Punch End Time on Lysithea
  • Input Timesheet for the day on Lysithea


Related Information

1. Requirements 

Make sure that the following requirements are met

  • Use PC and IT devices lent by company
  • Have the right infrastructure and security protocol in place
  • Take care not to leak personal information or trade secrets always
  • Follow Information security guidelines
  • Can communicate timely with your team members
  • Not working in public space.  (Make sure to work from your "home")

2. Notes

  • You can not charge overhead costs, such as personal utility expenses, communication costs, stationary or rent to the company
  • Injuries or sickness that occur while working from Home are outside the scope of compensation  based upon the Industrial Accident Compensation Insurance Act, depending on the situation

All KIT members are not allowed to work in places other than those listed below.

[Appropriate Workplace]

  1. KIT Office
  2. Home
  3. Client or other business outing
    ​​​​​​​

If you need to temporarily work in a place other than those listed above due to personal reasons, please consult with your Division head first.

KIT provides specific equipments for working from home as a rental.


Please read Rental Equipment to see more detail.
You can also directly jump to the Request Forms.

Work at the Office section expanded

Work at the Office

Flow

Submit KIT 2.0 Desk Reservation APP in advance if you are planning to use Reserved Seat at the office

When you are working at the office, it's your choice to take a seat from either Reserved Seat / Non-Reserved Seat
Please refer below seating MAP and check where each seat is placed at.
*For those who have dedicated seat or seating at Non-Reserved Seat, doesn't need to submit the APP anymore

 

[How to submit the APP]

 

 

  • Punch Start Time on Lysithea
  • Punch End Time on Lysithea
  • Input Timesheet for the day on Lysithea


Related Information

  • Sharing space with AZ Digital Innovation Team/Advisory Light House

    - We share office space with DI and ALH
       As for the free desk and concentrated booth, there are seats that requires reservation and seats that non required reservation,
       so please make a reservation in advance using the app if you are seating at reservation required seat

    - We share printer and other office equipment  with DI and ALH
     


  • Keep tidiness around your desk
    When You leave your seat
    • Don't leave confidential documents on your desk when you leave.
    • Leave PC after screen lock
              Win: (Ctrl+Alt+Delete）/ Mac:(control + command + Q)
    • Carry your iPhone or put it in your bag without leaving it on your desk
    Clear desk
    • Keep your desk tidy
    • Do not place files at your feet
    Clear screen
    • Do not store files on the clear screen PC desktop
    • Do not place files or folders containing Sensitive or more sensitive information in the PC Recycle Bin
    • (Win) Do not use screen savers and wallpaper other than the KPMG standard for loaned PCs.


  • Wearing ID card

    - You are required to keep wearing your ID card all the time when you are in the office
       We provide neck strap with your ID card so please have an employee ID card on a neck strap

When you are coming to the office, you need to have a security card to getting inside the office.
Most of employees are already received their individual ID card on their first day when they joined KIT
however some of the people may not be received yet due to avoid coming to the office for Covid-19 measures.
For those who are planning to come to the office for the first time, please reach out to KIT GA members.

The other inquireries that relevant to ID/Security Card, please read Security Card for your reference.
You are available to find following topics from above page.

  • Usage rules
  • Types of security cards
  • Areas accessible with the card
  • Loss or damage of the card
  • Borrowing a security card

You are required to submit your expense report include commuting expense on a monthly basis.
All expense report should be submitted by Concur.

Click Expenses to check the guidance and other related rules.
